Fix for for nested withConfig (issue #447). Includes tests.

Fix for for nested withConfig (issue #447). Includes tests.

When nesting calls to withConfig, deep copying config causes an
unbounded loop/stack exception as config.configuration references
config itself. Passing config through _.omit to filter out
.configuration prior to deep copying resolves this issue.

errorInterceptor does not intercept very well. Let the hook prevent the following actions.

Setting an errorInterceptor function does not prevent the normal execution of the flow.
Basically there is no way to prevent the data to reach the normal hooks.

With this patch, which is backward compatible and should not introduce any regression, when tie errorInterceptor returns false (instead of the traditional response) the response does not reach the following hooks.

As an example, if the API returns a 403 Unauthorized response, i cannot have a single hook to redirect the user to the login page.
With this patch i could intercept every call and prevent the normal flow execution.

Merge pull request #82 from ryankshaw/patch-1

update plunkr example to not flash empty <inputs> when editing

update plunkr example with one that does flash empty <inputs> that say 'required' when editing

in your original plunkr, when you click to edit a project it transitions to the 'edit' page immediately (before the request to fetch the resource from the API comes back) so it would have blank inputs for a period of time and have red 'required' next to each (until the request comes back). this changes the plunker to move it up into the 'resolve' hook in $routeProvider so it waits for the request to respond before rendering the edit action so you don't have the periodic flash of blank inputs.  I think it makes the code look more clean too.
